I am really speechless, but not in a good way. As a start let us agree that when a person decides to have lunch or dinner in a restaurant whether through being in the place or asking the food to be delivered, this person will be expecting the best of the best or at least that the food he will be having is going to be better than that this person prepares at home. Another point, when a person pays almost 300 pounds in a meal, he will be waiting for a unique food experience that will be worth that money paid for it. Well, my food experience with the restaurant wasn't that nice at all, really if it wasn't for my beloved mother, I wouldn't have ordered anything from you. The dolma tasted weird, some were salty, and others were almost empty and finally one or two tasted well. I don't know how such a collection of tastes can happen in one dish. it's very strange. As for the negresco, I really make it better at home at least I will be using fresh mushrooms, and there will be more chicken with the proper spices to make it delicious. Overall, from my experience, your dishes are highly overpriced putting into consideration primarily the quality that you are offering and secondly the presence of many restaurants around you which are offering your same menu BUT with some much lower prices and far higher quality. I am sorry, I don't think I will be trying to get anything from your restaurant again, this was my final time.
